\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}2 pounds very fresh tuna steak, cut 1-inch thick\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 tablespoons {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/olive-oil/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 olive oil}}, plus extra for brushing\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 1/2 teaspoons kosher salt, plus extra for sprinkling\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon coarsely ground black, plus extra for sprinkling\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 limes, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/zest/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 zest}} grated\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon wasabi powder\
{\listtext	\'95	}6 tablespoons freshly squeezed lime juice (3 limes)\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/soy-sauce/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 soy sauce}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}10 dashes hot sauce (recommended: Tabasco)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 to 2 ripe Hass {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/avocado/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 avocados}}, medium diced\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup minced {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/scallion/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 scallions}}, white and green parts (2 scallions)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup red onion, small diced\
