\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Brush the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/tuna/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 tuna steaks}} with olive oil, and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place the tuna steaks in a very hot saute pan and cook for only 1 minute on each side. Set aside on a platter.\
Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine the olive oil, salt, pepper, lime zest, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/wasabi/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 wasabi}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/lime/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 lime}} juice, soy sauce and hot sauce. Add the avocados to the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/vinaigrette/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 vinaigrette}}.\
Cut the tuna in chunks and place it in a large bowl. Add the scallions and red {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/onion/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 onion}} and mix well. Pour the vinaigrette mixture over the tuna and carefully mix.}